                "invention-title": [
                    "Process for catalyzing direct hydrogenation decomposition reduction of carbonate based on iron-containing solid waste",
                    "一种基于含铁固废催化碳酸盐直接加氢分解还原的工艺"
                ]
            },
            "abstract": [
                {
                    "p": "The invention provides a process for catalyzing direct hydrogenation decomposition reduction of carbonate based on iron-containing solid waste. The iron-containing solid waste is doped into a carbonate raw material, then calcination decomposition reduction is performed under the condition that hydrogen donor molecules are introduced, metal oxide can be obtained at a relatively low temperature, in-situ capture and conversion of CO2 are achieved, remarkable emission reduction and consumption reduction potential is achieved, the added solid waste can be directly used in the production process of cement, refractory materials and the like, and the production cost is reduced. And a'catalyst 'separation treatment is not needed. According to the new technological process, high-value utilization of solid waste, energy conservation and consumption reduction in the carbonate decomposition process and CO2 in-situ conversion and utilization are achieved, and important practical significance and wide industrial application prospects are achieved."
                },
                {
                    "p": "本发明提供一种基于含铁固废催化碳酸盐直接加氢分解还原的工艺。将含铁固废掺入碳酸盐原料中，随后在通入供氢分子的条件下进行煅烧分解还原，可以在相对较低的温度下获得金属氧化物，并实现CO2的原位捕集和转化，具有显著的减排降耗潜力，所添加的固废可直接用作水泥、耐材等生产过程，无需进行“催化剂”分离处理。该新工艺过程实现了固废的高值利用和碳酸盐分解过程的节能降耗和CO2原位转化利用，具有重要的现实意义和广阔的工业应用前景。"
                }
            ]
        }
